==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[firm&#257;mentum]]'' "firmament" from ''[[firmus]]'' "firm"

=== Noun ===
'''firmament'''
# the [[vault]] of the [[heavens]]; the [[sky]]
#: ''And God said, "Let there be a '''firmament''' in the midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters."''
# ''obsolete'' : [[basis]]
3 : the field or sphere of an interest or activity <the international fashion firmament>
=== Adjective ===
'''firmamental'''
# of or relating to the firmament
#: ''the '''firmamental''' stone left a scorched hole to mark its [[terrestrial]] grave''

==== Antonyms ====
*[[terrestrial]]

